8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 830, L.D. 1255, “An Act to Ensure In-
10 state Tuition for Postsecondary Students Who Are Registered to Vote in the State and to
11 Amend Eligibility Requirements for the Free Community College Tuition Program”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Require That an Individual Enrolled in the Free Community College
14 Tuition Program Lives in the State Prior to Enrollment at a Community College'
15 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.
16 Amend the bill in section 2 in that part designated Sec. QQQ-3 in subsection 2 by
17 striking out all of paragraph B-1 (page 2, lines 9 and 10 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
18 'B-1. Reside in the State for at least one year prior to enrollment in a Maine community
19 college;'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, reduces a person's
2244 residence requirement in the State prior to enrollment in a Maine community college in
2255 order to be eligible for free tuition in the Maine Community College System from at least
2266 2 years in the bill to at least one year. The amendment also removes from eligibility being
2277 a graduate of a high school in the State in lieu of the residency requirement. The amendment
2288 removes all provisions in the bill that would have provided in-state tuition rates at
2299 postsecondary schools to students registered to vote in the State.
